   1. Extract ncSOS zip into a local directory
   2. Copy the ncSOS.jar into the thredds/WEB-INF/lib directory.
   3. Copy the sos-servlet.xml configuration file into the thredds/WEB-INF/ directory.
   4. Add new servlet mappings to thredds/WEB-INF/web.xml with the following:

              <!-- sos services -->
              <servlet>
                <servlet-name>sos</servlet-name>
                <servlet-class>org.springframework.web.servlet.DispatcherServlet</servlet-class>
                <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>
              </servlet>

              <servlet-mapping>
                <servlet-name>sos</servlet-name>
                <url-pattern>/sos/*</url-pattern>
              </servlet-mapping>

   5. Add the following service definition to enable SOS in your THREDDS catalog XML files:

              <service name="sos" serviceType="SOS" base="/thredds/sos/" />
      		
   6. Restart the web application server.


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Feature Type ncSOS

    One thredds has been deployed on to the Apache Server

   1. Extract ncSOS zip into a local directory
   2. Copy the ncSOS.jar into the "thredds/WEB-INF/lib" directory.
   3. Copy the "sos-servlet.xml" configuration file into the "thredds/WEB-INF/" directory.
   4. Make sure there is a directory called "templates" containing *.xml templates in the "thredds/" directory.
   5. Add new servlet mappings to thredds/WEB-INF/web.xml with the following:

              <!-- sos services -->
              <servlet>
                <servlet-name>sos</servlet-name>
                <servlet-class>org.springframework.web.servlet.DispatcherServlet</servlet-class>
                <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>
              </servlet>

              <servlet-mapping>
                <servlet-name>sos</servlet-name>
                <url-pattern>/sos/*</url-pattern>
              </servlet-mapping>              

   6. Add the following service definition to enable SOS in your THREDDS catalog XML files:

              <service name="sos" serviceType="SOS" base="/thredds/sos/" />
      		
   7. Restart the web application server.